    "costs": "29000",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Safety standdown initiated at 16:14",
      "General alarm sounded at 16:41",
      "Full muster completed at 16:54",
      "Airgas HAZMAT response team vented cylinders starting at 22:16",
      "Three injured personnel evaluated by rig medic and cleared to return to work",
      "Operator plans to install nitrogen generation system in 2025 budget",
      "Helix plans to install physical barrier and hard piping",
      "Vendor change implemented"
    ],
    "summary": "On June 5, 2024, at approximately 15:38 hours, a nitrogen cylinder ruptured inside a twelve-cylinder bottle rack onboard the Helix Q5000 during workover operations. The rupture was caused by severe corrosion that reduced wall thickness from 0.25 inches to 0.075 inches at the bottom of the bottle, which contained approximately 2,400 psi. The rupture damaged other cylinders in the rack and scattered them across the main deck. Three personnel staging equipment nearby sustained minor injuries from shrapnel. The incident resulted in $29,000 in damage to 2 nitrogen racks and an umbilical. Investigation revealed inadequate corrosion protection from water-based paint coating, insufficient inspection protocols that did not include disassembly for thorough examination, poor rack design allowing metal-to-metal contact, and lack of drainage causing prolonged exposure to corrosive marine environment.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE New Orleans District recommends Office of Incident Investigations consider a Safety Alert to warn industry about the risk that these bottle racks pose",
      "Install nitrogen generation system to eliminate reliance on external rental systems",
      "Install physical barrier and hard piping to mitigate exposure to personnel and equipment during potential future failures",
      "Change vendor and adhere to elevated inspection process",
      "Implement inspection protocols that include disassembly for thorough examination of individual cylinders and manifold components",
      "Use corrosion-resistant coatings suitable for marine environment",
      "Design racks with proper drainage and material barriers between cylinders and rack structure"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "nitrogen bottle rupture",
      "corrosion led to wall loss",
      "wall thickness as thin as 0.075 in",
      "water-based paint coating failed",
      "metal-to-metal contact",
      "lack of drainage",
      "visual pre-fill inspections",
      "rack was not disassembled",
      "marine environment",
      "DOT special permit regulations"
    ]
  },
